Consider the sequence [`5, 9, 13, 17, 21, \ldots`] with [`a_1 = 5`]
a.  Give a recursive definition for the sequence.

a.  Give a closed formula for the [`n`]th term of the sequence.

a.  Is [`2013`] a term in the sequence? Explain.

a.  How many terms does the sequence [`5, 9, 13, 17, 21, \ldots, 533`] have?

a.  Find the sum: [`5 + 9 + 13 + 17 + 21 + \cdots + 533\text{.}`] Show your work.

a.  Use what you found above to find [`b_n\text{,}`] the [`n^{th}`] term of [`1, 6, 15, 28, 45, \ldots\text{,}`] where [`b_0 = 1`]

